a temper as renders their di&s;appointments
more light and ea&s;y than tho&s;e of other men.
If it does not bani&s;h di&s;&s;atisfaction from
their worldly plea&s;ures, it confers &s;piritual
plea&s;ures in their &s;tead. If it en&s;$res them
