<HI>Troubled on every &s;ide, yet not di&s;tre&s;&s;ed;
perplexed, but not in de&s;pair; per&s;ecuted, but
not for&s;aken; ca&s;t down, but not de&s;troyed.
For though our outward man peri&s;h, our in|ward
man is renewed, day by day</HI><NOTE N="&ast;" PLACE="foot">2 Corinth. iv. 8, 9. 16.</NOTE> Such,
though perhaps in an inferior degree, will
